    <fr:title text="Components">Components</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
The <html:strong>components</html:strong> of a compound sentence are the sentences combined by its main connective.
There are as many components as the arity of that main connective.
Atomic sentences do not have any components.

When a sentence's main connective is binary, it has two components, which are called its <html:strong>left component</html:strong> and its <html:strong>right component</html:strong>.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
