                <fr:title text="Special names for components">Special names for components</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
Depending on the main connective of a sentence, there are special names sometimes given to its components:
</html:p>
                <html:ul><html:li>when a sentence is a conjunction, its components are called its <html:strong>conjuncts</html:strong>;</html:li>
<html:li>when a sentence is a disjunction, its components are called its <html:strong>disjuncts</html:strong>;</html:li>
<html:li>when a sentence is an implication, its left component is called its <html:strong>antecedent</html:strong>;</html:li>
<html:li>when a sentence is an implication, its right component is called its <html:strong>consequent</html:strong>; and</html:li>
<html:li>when a sentence is a negation, its component is called its <html:strong>negatum</html:strong>.</html:li></html:ul>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
